---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <article class="about-page">
    <header class="about-header">
      <p class="about-kicker">A little more context</p>
      <h1>About me</h1>
      <p class="about-lede">
        I’m Tien, a platform operations engineer based in Vietnam. I like
        dependable systems, useful tools, and understanding why things fail.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section aria-labelledby="path-heading">
      <h2 id="path-heading">How I got here</h2>

      <p>
        My background is in biotechnology and bioinformatics rather than
        traditional computer science. I completed a BSc in Biotechnology in
        Singapore in 2017, followed by an MSc in Bioinformatics and
        Computational Biology in Ireland in 2019.
      </p>

      <p>
        I later entered a PhD programme, but left in 2023 after deciding it was
        no longer the right path for me. It was a difficult and sad decision,
        but also a deliberate one. It gave me space to reconsider the kind of
        work I actually wanted to do.
      </p>

      <div class="timeline" aria-label="Education and career timeline">
        <div>
          <span class="timeline-year">2017</span>
          <p>BSc in Biotechnology, completed in Singapore.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="timeline-year">2019</span>
          <p>MSc in Bioinformatics and Computational Biology in Ireland.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="timeline-year">2023</span>
          <p>Left academia and moved more deliberately toward engineering.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="timeline-year">Now</span>
          <p>Platform operations, reliability, automation, and scientific software.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="work-heading">
      <h2 id="work-heading">What I work on</h2>

      <p>
        I started around scientific research, biological data, and computational
        workflows. Over time, I became increasingly interested in the engineering
        underneath them:
      </p>

      <ul class="question-list">
        <li>Why did this job fail after running for two days?</li>
        <li>Why can nobody reproduce this environment?</li>
        <li>Where did the storage disappear?</li>
        <li>Why is this process still retrying after a month?</li>
        <li>How do we make the system easier to operate next time?</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        That gradually pulled me toward Linux systems, cloud infrastructure,
        distributed workloads, automation, observability, and reliability
        engineering.
      </p>

      <p>
        Today, I investigate production failures, build operational tooling,
        improve cloud usage, document failure modes, and help make complicated
        systems less fragile. I do not think reliability means that nothing ever
        fails. It means failures are visible, understandable, recoverable, and
        less likely to surprise the next person.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="outside-heading">
      <h2 id="outside-heading">Outside work</h2>

      <p>
        I like coffee, photography, and simple things that reward attention.
        I especially like sunlight passing through leaves—the Japanese word
        <em>komorebi</em> describes it better than I can.
      </p>

      <p>
        I also have a soft spot for mechanical things: watches, cars, tools, and
        machines whose behaviour can be observed and understood. Perhaps that is
        part of why systems engineering appeals to me. I like things that are
        dependable, maintainable, and honest about how they work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-card" aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <p class="contact-prompt">~/say-hello</p>
      <h2 id="contact-heading">Open to thoughtful conversations</h2>

      <p>
        I’m happy to hear from people working on platform operations, reliability,
        Linux and cloud infrastructure, scientific software, automation,
        developer tooling, technical writing, or small open-source projects.
      </p>

      <div class="contact-links">
        <a href="mailto:tiendu107@gmail.com">send an email</a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tiendu"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tienhdu"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          LinkedIn
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    margin-inline: auto;
    max-width: var(--content-width);
  }

  .about-header {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about-kicker {
    color: var(--brand);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    margin-block: 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-lede {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .about-page section + section {
    margin-top: 3.25rem;
  }

  .about-page section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .timeline {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border);
    margin-block: 1.75rem 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .timeline > div {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.25rem 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: 4rem minmax(0, 1fr);
    padding-block: 0.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline > div::before {
    background: var(--background);
    border: 2px solid var(--brand);
    border-radius: 50%;
    content: "";
    height: 10px;
    left: calc(-1.25rem - 6px);
    position: absolute;
    top: 1.05rem;
    width: 10px;
  }

  .timeline-year {
    color: var(--brand);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .timeline p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .question-list {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    list-style: none;
    margin-block: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 680px;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
  }

  .question-list li {
    padding-left: 1.35rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .question-list li::before {
    color: var(--brand);
    content: ">";
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    left: 0;
    position: absolute;
  }

  .question-list li + li {
    margin-top: 0.45rem;
  }

  .contact-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .contact-prompt {
    color: var(--brand);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .contact-card h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }

  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.6rem 1.15rem;
    margin-top: 1.15rem;
  }

  .contact-links a {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .contact-links a::before {
    content: "→ ";
  }

  @media (max-width: 650px) {
    .about-header {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .about-lede {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    .about-page section + section {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }

    .timeline > div {
      grid-template-columns: 3.5rem minmax(0, 1fr);
    }

    .contact-card {
      padding: 1.15rem;
    }

    .contact-links {
      align-items: flex-start;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.45rem;
    }
  }
</style>
